{
  "texts": [
    "ADA-cosine: similar to SBERT-cosine but employs the recent openAI model ada002.",
    "The value of τ used here is consistent with the one in Sec.5.2.",
    "SelfCheckGPT with Prompt: utilizes the same F LLM in each task, SelfCheckGPT generates additional N stochastic LLM response samples, denoted as S 1, S 2,..., S n, using the same query.",
    "Then, it scores the consistency between the generated response and the stochastic samples, by querying an LLM to determine whether the i-th sentence in A * is supported by the corresponding sample S i.",
    "The final inconsistency score is computed by averaging the sentence scores."
  ]
}